Assets.Name: BlankBuildingMap
Assets.Description:
Blank level with Map Editor Mod

Controls:
WASD / left stick - move the camera
Mouse / right stick - rotate the camera
Q,E / left/right trigger - move the camera up/down
Backspace / X, Square - Delete piece
Left Click / A, Cross - Place piece
R / Y, Triangle - Toggle Snapping
Mouse Wheel / D-pad Up, Down - Switch piece
Z, X / D-pad Left, Right - Rotate piece
Shift / LB, L1 - Move Faster "Sprint"
Tab / View, Select - Open Save/Load Menu
Keyboard B / RB + Left Stick Click Twice, R1 + Left Stick Click Twice - Open/Close Build Mode

You can toggle through different building pieces that can be snapped together, or free places. In the save/load menu, you can also toggle on the session NYC background for some added city life feel. 

The save is based off of the name of your level. The save and/or level name can be changed and shared with friends to skate or continue adding to it.
Assets.Author: Travis Bragg#5150

Assets.Name: CustomizableBlankDecks
Assets.Description:
this mod adds 50 deck graphics variations that are shared between all the blank decks in this mod so you can have the size of deck you want with the graphic you want       

you can set the 50 deck graphics with a texture or with a material

the path to textures is Content\CustomDeckGraphics\Textures    and name your textures 001 - 050
the path to materials is Content\CustomDeckGraphics\Materials  and name your materials MAI_DG_001 - MAI_DG_050

DONT REPLACE MATERIAL   MAI_DG_001  ,  TEXTURE 000  AND  ICON TEX_DG_000_ICON  
MAI_DG_001 is used for the blank decks   
Texture 000 is the default texture when you don't have a deck graphic assigned to one of the variations
TEX_DG_000_ICON  is the icon used for all the blank decks 


if try out this mod and you find any problems with it let me know so i can fix it or if you cant figure out how to use it let me know and ill help you out with it

Assets.Name: TDV_PinDropper
Assets.Description:
**"Pin Dropper Mod"** **Update**
Replaces Security Light

**INSTRUCTIONS**
install through SMM in the gear sections. Replaces the Security Light object in the object dropper (first item)
Place a single object (it is invisible and has collision, can place it out of the way in the level)

Once the object has been placed --
Hold RB/R1 and click right stick to spawn dropper, again to spawn skater at pin dropper location
Left stick -  move dropper
Right stick - move camera
Triggers - Move up/down
Left bumper - Hold to move faster

**Recommended to get off board before using**

Fixed respawn causing fatal error while using pin dropper.

Fire Dropper mod
Replaces wooden kicker

walk up and press E when standing in it to toggle through the 18 different fires. 
will save and automatically load the chosen fire each time you start the map.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jUFcv9uE606H4zUwEPIaa6nbnLLvq9zf/view?usp=sharing
Assets.Author: Travis Bragg#5150

Assets.Name: TDV_ModLoader
Assets.Description:
TDV_ModLoader

I have restructured the way my mods will be working and this will be required to load any, and will be updated singularly if any new types of mods are added. 



**Instructions**
Install through SMM in the gear sections. Replaces the Security Light object in the object dropper (first item)
Place a single object (it is invisible and has collision, can place it out of the way in the level) **<<<will be changing this soon**
Once the object is placed, it will auto load all other TDV mods you have installed.

As of this post, this is required to spawn:
TDV_PinDropperMod
TDV_PhysicsMenu
TDV_RMSLoader

Assets.Name: TDV_RMSLoader
Assets.Description:
TDV_RMSLoader

**Requires "TDV_ModLoader"**

**Instructions**
Follow TDV_ModLoader instructions to make this spawnable
Installs through the gear section of SMM

Upon loading into a level, If the level does not currently support the <@414939259267448832> toolsuite, this mod will load it and create a new save based off the name of the current level to allow toolsuite functionality and saving/loading your spawned NPC's.

Many thanks to <@414939259267448832> for his mod and the help to make sure this loader works properly for the map makers who have not currently added support for his toolsuite.
